  "ai_usage": "Use for any content image to improve perceived performance and prevent layout shift. Wrap the image in a box with a fixed aspect-ratio; render a tiny LQIP (base64 or dominant color) scaled up + blurred behind it; when the full <img> fires load, fade it in over the placeholder. Keep real alt text on the <img>, aria-hide the placeholder, and respect reduced motion for the fade.",
  "path": "effects/images-media/blur-up-load.html",
  "source": "<!DOCTYPE html>\n<html lang=\"en\">\n<head>\n  <meta charset=\"UTF-8\" />\n  <meta name=\"viewport\" content=\"width=device-width, initial-scale=1\" />\n  <title>Blur-Up Image Load</title>\n  <script type=\"application/json\" id=\"effect-meta\">\n  {\n    \"id\": \"blur-up-load\",\n    \"title\": \"Blur-Up Image Load\",\n    \"summary\": \"The progressive 'blur-up': a tiny blurred placeholder sharpens into the full image as it loads — no layout jank, perceived speed.\",\n    \"description\": \"The LQIP / blur-up technique used by Next.js, Medium, and Unsplash: show a tiny, upscaled, blurred preview immediately, then crossfade to the sharp image on load. This demo simulates the load with a button so you can replay it.\",\n    \"theme\": \"images-media\",\n    \"categories\": [\"image\", \"loading\", \"performance\"],\n    \"tags\": [\"blur-up\", \"lqip\", \"placeholder\", \"lazy\", \"progressive\", \"performance\"],\n    \"tech\": [\"css\", \"js\"],\n    \"era\": \"2020s\",\n    \"difficulty\": \"beginner\",\n    \"dependencies\": [],\n    \"browser_support\": \"All modern browsers.\",\n    \"performance_notes\": \"The placeholder is a tiny inline gradient/data-URI scaled up and blurred; swapping to the full image removes the blur. Reserve the box with aspect-ratio to avoid layout shift.\",\n    \"accessibility_notes\": \"Always give the real <img> meaningful alt text; the blurred layer is aria-hidden. The box uses aspect-ratio so there's no CLS. Crossfade respects prefers-reduced-motion.\",\n    \"customization\": [\n      { \"name\": \"placeholder\", \"description\": \"Tiny LQIP / dominant-color blur\", \"default\": \"gradient stand-in\" },\n      { \"name\": \"--fade\", \"description\": \"Crossfade duration\", \"default\": \"0.6s\" }\n    ],\n    \"variations\": [\"Dominant-color block instead of blur\", \"Shimmer skeleton during load\", \"Pixelated (no blur) reveal\"],\n    \"related\": [\"skeleton-loader\", \"ken-burns\", \"duotone-image\"],\n    \"ai_usage\": \"Use for any content image to improve perceived performance and prevent layout shift. Wrap the image in a box with a fixed aspect-ratio; render a tiny LQIP (base64 or dominant color) scaled up + blurred behind it; when the full <img> fires load, fade it in over the placeholder. Keep real alt text on the <img>, aria-hide the placeholder, and respect reduced motion for the fade.\"\n  }\n  </script>\n  <style>\n    :root{--fade:.6s;}\n    html,body{height:100%;margin:0}\n    body{display:grid;place-items:center;gap:1rem;background:#0b0d12;color:#e8ecf6;font-family:system-ui,sans-serif}\n    .frame{position:relative;width:min(420px,90vw);aspect-ratio:3/2;border-radius:16px;overflow:hidden;background:#11131b}\n    .lqip{position:absolute;inset:0;filter:blur(18px);transform:scale(1.1);\n      background:linear-gradient(135deg,#5b3ea8,#c0552f 45%,#1b6b7a)}\n    .full{position:absolute;inset:0;opacity:0;transition:opacity var(--fade) ease;\n      background:\n        radial-gradient(circle at 30% 30%,#a78bff,transparent 40%),\n        radial-gradient(circle at 75% 60%,#ffb454,transparent 45%),\n        linear-gradient(135deg,#6d4ec9,#c0552f 45%,#1b8aa0);\n      display:grid;place-items:center;color:#fff;font-weight:800;font-size:1.3rem;text-shadow:0 2px 12px rgba(0,0,0,.4)}\n    .full.loaded{opacity:1}\n    button{background:#7c5cff;color:#fff;border:none;border-radius:10px;padding:.6rem 1.2rem;font-weight:700;cursor:pointer}\n    button:focus-visible{outline:3px solid #2dd4bf;outline-offset:2px}\n    @media(prefers-reduced-motion:reduce){.full{transition:none}}\n  </style>\n</head>\n<body>\n  <div class=\"frame\">\n    <div class=\"lqip\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></div>\n    <div class=\"full\" id=\"full\" role=\"img\" aria-label=\"A colorful gradient photograph\">Sharp image ✶</div>\n  </div>\n  <button id=\"reload\">▶ Simulate load</button>\n  <script>\n    var full=document.getElementById('full'),reload=document.getElementById('reload');\n    function load(){ full.classList.remove('loaded'); setTimeout(function(){full.classList.add('loaded');},900); }\n    reload.addEventListener('click',load);\n    load();\n  </script>\n</body>\n</html>\n"
}
